<div class="letter">
  <div class="letter-inner">

    <p class="letter-opening">She's the Goose was created from the belief that a home does not need to be perfect to feel beautiful.</p>

    <p>A good lamp in the corner. Dinner cooking before the guests arrive. Flowers from the grocery store dropped into a heavy vase. Linens wrinkled from being used often. A kitchen that looks lived in, not staged.</p>

    <p>This is a collection of recipes, objects, gatherings, and details that make everyday life feel warmer, slower, and more intentional.</p>

    <p>Some things are old. Some are new. Some are investment pieces. Some are simple finds that work just as well. Nothing is shared here unless it has earned a place in my own home — used, kept, and quietly returned to.</p>

    <p>She's the Goose is the more tangible side of this way of living. Its sister publication, <a href="https://thequietledger.co" target="_blank" class="inline-link">The Quiet Ledger</a>, is where the writing lives — seasonal letters, recipes, and the slower, longer form of the same ideas.</p>

    <p>Together, they are simply my way of thinking about home.</p>

    <p class="letter-signature">— Jessica</p>

  </div>
</div>

